e English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born in 1177. She had at least 1 son with Sir Asceline Sydenham of Titchmarsh."},"et":{"1177–":"1177–Surnud","1173–1225":"1173–1225","1200–1233":"1200–1233","1177–Female":"1177–Surnud","1225":"1225","1233":"1233","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1173":"1173","Sydenham, Somerset, England":"Sydenham, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1177–":"1177–Kuollut","1173–1225":"1173–1225","1200–1233":"1200–1233","1177–Female":"1177–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1233":"1233","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","about 1200":"noin 1200","1173":"1173","Sydenham, Somerset, England":"Sydenham, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"1177–":"1177–Décédée","1173–1225":"1173–1225","1200–1233":"1200–1233","1177–Female":"1177–Décédée","1225":"1225","1233":"1233","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","about 1200":"environ 1200","1173":"1173","Sydenham, Somerset, England":"Sydenham, Somerset, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Joan est née en 1177. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir Asceline Sydenham of Titchmarsh."},"de":{"1177–":"1177–Verstorben","1173–1225":"1173–1225","1200–1233":"1200–1233","1177–Female":"1177–Verstorben","1225":"1225","1233":"1233","1200":"1200","1177":"1177","about 1200":"um 1200","1173":"1173","Sydenham, Somerset, England":"Sydenham, Somerset, England","lifeSummary":"Joan wur